We get some dramatic Lake Erie clouds, but rarely something this amazing. On a stop in Nebraska, I did see a line of clouds move toward the motel during a tornado warning--it was memorable but nothing hit the ground.  As a kid in Iowa, I saw the aftermath destruction of tornados taking down barns and trees but missed the action harbored in the basement.  Love your photos.
